{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0094-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Active Text Performance Regression & Fix",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1741564800000,
  "modified": 1775756672379,
  "content": {
    "tags": [
      "bff75873-edb8-412e-81c9-c744e68fe29f",
      "c0c0c0c0-0081-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "c0c0c0c0-0085-0000-0000-000000000000"
    ],
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "After bulk-migrating item descriptions from markdown strings to "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":doc"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " ASTs, startup went from near-instant to ~4 s and Ctrl+K became unusably slow. This documents the root causes and fixes."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Root cause: Hob interpreter overhead on structural data"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The core issue was not data size (ASTs are only ~1.6× larger than equivalent markdown). It was that code paths which previously touched a single string per item were now recursively walking deeply nested arrays — and some of that recursion ran inside the Hob interpreter rather than native JS."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Five contributing problems"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "1. compact-card-view: Hob-interpreted AST walk (primary Ctrl+K bottleneck)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Every search result and starred item rendered through "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "d4e5f6a7-b8c9-4d0e-a1b2-c3d4e5f6a7b8"
          },
          {
            "s": "compact-card-view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", which extracted preview text from descriptions. Before the migration, descriptions were strings — the extract was a no-op. After, it ran a recursive Hob function over every AST node: ~100 interpreter calls per item × 10+ items = 1000+ Hob evaluations just for preview text."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Fix: Added a JS-native "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "extract-text"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " stdlib function and replaced the Hob "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "extract"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " function with a single call to it."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "2. related-items-lib: deep recursive regex scan (startup bottleneck)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "f5f8535c-8db9-4bff-a810-28174b77235c"
          },
          {
            "s": "related-items-lib"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "'s "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "extractLinks"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " scanned every string in every item's content with a regex looking for "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "item://"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " URLs. Two problems: (a) Active Text documents have ~37× more string nodes than a single markdown string, so the regex ran ~13,000 times at startup; (b) "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "item://"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " links no longer exist in the AST — they're represented structurally as "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":item-ref"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " nodes."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Fix: Rewrote "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "extractLinks"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to walk the AST structurally for "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":item-ref"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " nodes, and only regex-scan "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.code"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.body"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " strings where legacy links may still exist."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "3. item-search-lib: JSON.stringify + expensive filter path"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "buildSearchableText"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " called "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "JSON.stringify(item.content)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " on every item for every search. With larger AST content, this was dramatically slower. The filter-syntax path (triggered by "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "type:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "tag:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "name:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " etc.) also rebuilt type/tag caches from scratch on every keystroke, even when the query didn't use them."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Fix: Replaced JSON.stringify with targeted field extraction. Parse the query first, only build caches the query actually needs, return empty for incomplete filters like "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "name:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Added synchronous filter matching for the common case."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "4. item-palette: sequential blocking before modal display"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "f1111111-0005-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "item-palette"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " did 6 sequential async operations before showing the modal: query, get, require, getStarredItems (full getAll + filter + sort), set (DB write + events + re-render), attach."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Fix: Removed starred pre-fetch and require — the search view already handles this. Used "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "silent: true"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for the state reset to skip the redundant event/render cycle."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "5. Views calling render-markdown on AST data"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "b7f3a1d2-8e5c-4f6a-9d0b-1c2e3f4a5b6c"
          },
          {
            "s": "note-widget-view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "b15db8aa-1e48-478a-9455-24a31ca9d8ca"
          },
          {
            "s": "event-definition-view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " passed "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.description"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "render-markdown"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", which expects a string. With AST arrays this threw \"Input data should be a String\" errors."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Fix: Check if description is a "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":doc"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " AST and render it as hiccup directly; fall back to "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "render-markdown"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " only for legacy strings."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design lesson"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The Hob interpreter is not suitable for tight recursive data processing. Any function that walks a tree of arbitrary depth — text extraction, link scanning, serialization — must be implemented in JS and exposed as a stdlib function. The interpreter is for view logic and orchestration, not data crunching. This applies doubly when the function runs per-item in a list (O(items × AST_depth) interpreter calls)."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "More broadly: when migrating data formats, audit every code path that touches the changed fields — not just the ones that read/write them, but the ones that incidentally process them (search indexing, link extraction, preview generation, rendering). The regression was not in the Active Text renderer itself but in peripheral code that assumed string descriptions."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Items changed"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":item-ref",
            {
              "s": "40b00001-0000-4000-8000-000000000000"
            },
            {
              "s": "hob-stdlib"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " — new "
          },
          [
            ":code",
            {
              "s": "extract-text"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " function"
          }
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":item-ref",
            {
              "s": "d4e5f6a7-b8c9-4d0e-a1b2-c3d4e5f6a7b8"
            },
            {
              "s": "compact-card-view"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " — use "
          },
          [
            ":code",
            {
              "s": "extract-text"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " instead of Hob recursive extract"
          }
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":item-ref",
            {
              "s": "f5f8535c-8db9-4bff-a810-28174b77235c"
            },
            {
              "s": "related-items-lib"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " — structural "
          },
          [
            ":code",
            {
              "s": ":item-ref"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " walk instead of deep regex scan"
          }
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":item-ref",
            {
              "s": "6734035b-e30b-4c2a-829e-d57b3d1fd5dc"
            },
            {
              "s": "item-search-lib"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " — remove JSON.stringify, lazy cache building, sync filtering"
          }
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":item-ref",
            {
              "s": "f1111111-0005-0000-0000-000000000000"
            },
            {
              "s": "item-palette"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " — defer starred fetch, silent state reset"
          }
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":item-ref",
            {
              "s": "b7f3a1d2-8e5c-4f6a-9d0b-1c2e3f4a5b6c"
            },
            {
              "s": "note-widget-view"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " — handle Active Text descriptions"
          }
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":item-ref",
            {
              "s": "b15db8aa-1e48-478a-9455-24a31ca9d8ca"
            },
            {
              "s": "event-definition-view"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " — handle Active Text descriptions"
          }
        ]
      ]
    ]
  },
